lead_paragraph: The Japanese Government has forbidden "unofficial" celebrations today of the first anniversary of Japan's treaty with the Axis Powers. The prohibition could not have been necessary. Nothing has come of Berlin's solemn recognition of the "New Order in Greater East Asia."
